The paper discusses the use of convolutional nets for image analysis in the context of neural circuit reconstruction, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the challenges of handling image defects, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computational systems for handling large brain volumes, which could fall under the category of scientific computing (cs.SD).
